Hi, I'm Amy.

I like making things happen.

Make things matter. I’m a problem solver with a creative itch. I love designing experiences across design, data, and tech. I’m an L.A. girl with big dreams – I’m discovering mine studying computer science and psychology at Stanford. I’m currently launching products at Lenovo, bringing digital devices to everyone around the globe. Previously, I built data tools at the Census Bureau and Coding it Forward and designed for national political campaigns for Coding it Forward. I pride myself on bringing ethics and a deep love of research to the drawing board. For every pixel I push, I want to know how it’ll change people’s behavior, decisions, and minds. investigating why we make the decisions that we do and how that’s influenced by our communities. I’m just getting started in my journey, and I’m looking for opportunities that’ll make an impact. Reach out to me anytime – I’ll make it worth your while!
